node.text: Today is Earth Day. A day we reflect on the importance of our planet. A day we show appreciation for everything the Earth has given us. And a day we pause to consider our impact on the world...our home. This year, Earth Day has a deeper meaning. In recent months we’ve received a wake up call. Now more than ever we are reminded how we are all connected. So much of what we take for granted could be lost in an instant. But through hardship comes a deeper sense of compassion and sacrifice. While we are unable to freely explore, we’ll be back out there again soon with a deeper appreciation for what we have been missing. On this Earth Day, Mother Nature can catch her breath.  On this Earth Day, we remind you just how close you are to your neighbor. Our actions can ripple throughout this planet and it’s our responsibility to protect it. We only have on Earth! So let’s take care of it and let’s take care of eachother! Happy Earth Day! Thank you to everyone who made this video possible! ♥️🌎
